headers.subject: [tosdr:2572] Stack Exchange requires real name

html:
Subscriber shall provide Stack Exchange with accurate, complete, and updated registration information, including Subscriber’s e-mail address. Failure to do so shall constitute a breach of this Agreement, which may result in immediate termination of Subscriber's account.

http://stackexchange.com/legal

I'm not sure about this. On the one hand, it seems like providing truthful information is a no-brainer, but on the other hand, I'm not sure why it's required in the first place. Maybe if you are an active contributor, I suppose? A little discussion on this would help me better curate this particular point, I think.
